HEADWORD: Onycha
<hw>On"y*cha</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from L.
<ets>onyx</ets>, <ets>-ychis</ets>, onyx, also, a kind of mussel, Gr.
<?/, <?/. See <er>Onyx</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>An ingredient of the Mosaic incense, probably the
operculum of some kind of strombus.</def> <rj><au>Ex. xxx.
34.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The precious stone called
<altname>onyx</altname>.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Onychia</ent>⟦br⟧
